OL,3,CMore than 8,000 social media accounts
OL,4,Clinked to people smuggling taken down
OL,6,FSophie Austin, operations manager at
OL,7,Fthe NCA's Online Communication Centre,
OL,8,Fsaid: "Social media remains a key way
OL,9,Fthe organised crime groups involved in
OL,10,Fpeople smuggling promoting their
OL,11,Fillegal services to migrants.
OL,13,F"It is a major part of their business
OL,14,Fmodel.
OL,16,F"Once migrants are engaged they then
OL,17,Fmove conversations onto encrypted
OL,18,Fmessaging apps where they are hidden
OL,19,Ffrom law enforcement.
